# Snowflake Intelligence

This component configures the Cortex Agent and supporting services (Cortex Analyst + Cortex Search) that power the natural-language query interface.

## Architecture

```
User Question (natural language)
        │
        ▼
BUSINESS_INSIGHTS_AGENT (SEMANTIC schema)
  ├── query_business_data (cortex_analyst_text_to_sql)
  │     └── Semantic View: BUSINESS_ANALYTICS_SEMANTIC
  ├── search_reviews (cortex_search)
  │     └── PRODUCT_REVIEWS_SEARCH
  └── search_tickets (cortex_search)
        └── SUPPORT_TICKETS_SEARCH

Cortex Search (also available independently)
  ├── PRODUCT_REVIEWS_SEARCH (SEMANTIC schema, multi-index)
  ├── SUPPORT_TICKETS_SEARCH (SEMANTIC schema, multi-index)
  └── product_search_service (RAW schema, multi-index)
```

## Cortex Agent

The agent `BUSINESS_INSIGHTS_AGENT` uses the **CREATE AGENT ... FROM SPECIFICATION** API (March 2026) with a JSON spec that wires together text-to-SQL and search tools:

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE AGENT AUTOMATED_INTELLIGENCE.SEMANTIC.BUSINESS_INSIGHTS_AGENT
FROM SPECIFICATION $$
{
  "models": { "orchestration": "auto" },
  "tools": [
    { "tool_spec": { "type": "cortex_analyst_text_to_sql", "name": "query_business_data", ... } },
    { "tool_spec": { "type": "cortex_search", "name": "search_reviews", ... } },
    { "tool_spec": { "type": "cortex_search", "name": "search_tickets", ... } }
  ],
  "tool_resources": {
    "query_business_data": { "semantic_view": "AUTOMATED_INTELLIGENCE.SEMANTIC.BUSINESS_ANALYTICS_SEMANTIC" },
    "search_reviews": { "search_service": "AUTOMATED_INTELLIGENCE.SEMANTIC.PRODUCT_REVIEWS_SEARCH" },
    "search_tickets": { "search_service": "AUTOMATED_INTELLIGENCE.SEMANTIC.SUPPORT_TICKETS_SEARCH" }
  }
}
$$;
```

**Key agent spec structure**:
- **`tools`** — array of `tool_spec` objects (type, name, description)
- **`tool_resources`** — **separate top-level object** keyed by tool name (NOT nested inside tools)
- **`instructions`** — `orchestration` (routing guidance) + `response` (formatting guidance)
- **`orchestration.budget`** — seconds and token limits
- Tool types: `cortex_analyst_text_to_sql`, `cortex_search`, `generic` (stored procedures)

The agent creation SQL is in **`create_agent.sql`**.

### YAML Semantic Model (Legacy)

The legacy YAML file `business_insights_semantic_model.yaml` still exists on stage `@AUTOMATED_INTELLIGENCE.RAW.SEMANTIC_MODELS` but the agent now references the **SQL semantic view** `BUSINESS_ANALYTICS_SEMANTIC` instead. Two semantic views exist:

| Name | Location | Tables |
|------|----------|--------|
| `business_analytics_semantic` | `setup.sql:1066` | `RAW.ORDERS`, `RAW.CUSTOMERS`, `RAW.ORDER_ITEMS` |
| `ORDERS_ANALYTICS_SV` | `semantic_view_sql_demo.sql:22` | `RAW.ORDERS`, `RAW.CUSTOMERS` |

The agent references `business_analytics_semantic` via the `query_business_data` tool.

## Cortex Search Services (Multi-Index)

All three search services use **multi-index syntax** (GA March 12, 2026) with TEXT + VECTOR indexes:

| Service | Schema | TEXT INDEX | VECTOR INDEX | Model |
|---------|--------|-----------|-------------|-------|
| `product_search_service` | RAW | `product_name` | `description` | `snowflake-arctic-embed-m-v1.5` |
| `product_reviews_search` | SEMANTIC | `review_title` | `review_text` | `snowflake-arctic-embed-m-v1.5` |
| `support_tickets_search` | SEMANTIC | `subject` | `description` | `snowflake-arctic-embed-m-v1.5` |

```sql
-- Example: multi-index syntax (from create_postgres_search_services.sql)
CREATE OR REPLACE CORTEX SEARCH SERVICE SEMANTIC.PRODUCT_REVIEWS_SEARCH
    TEXT INDEXES review_title
    VECTOR INDEXES review_text (model='snowflake-arctic-embed-m-v1.5')
    ATTRIBUTES product_id, customer_id, rating, review_date
    WAREHOUSE = AUTOMATED_INTELLIGENCE_WH
    TARGET_LAG = '1 hour'
AS (
    SELECT review_id, product_id, customer_id, review_date, rating, review_title, review_text
    FROM RAW.PRODUCT_REVIEWS
);
```

**Note**: Multi-index requires at least one VECTOR INDEX. All services query `RAW.*` tables (not `POSTGRES.*`). TARGET_LAG is `1 hour`.

